  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Kdenetwork</title>

    <para>Install <application>kdenetwork</application> by running
    the following commands:</para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd build &amp;&amp;
cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=&kde-dir; \
      -DSYSCONF_INSTALL_DIR=/etc/kde \
      .. &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:</para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    <para><option>-DDISABLE_VIDEOSUPPORT=ON</option>: Set this option in case 
    you don't have <application>libv4l</application> installed.</para>

  </sect2>

